wiki.content: On “Yah Yah,” Eminem enlists fellow emcees Royce da 5'9", Black Thought and Q-Tip for a posse cut over an upbeat boom-bap instrumental, produced by featured artist dEnAun. Over a near five-minute runtime, the rappers pay homage to inspirational hip-hop veterans and display their lyrical prowess. Interestingly, each of the featured artists are part of a different rap group; Royce da 5'9" is from Slaughterhouse, Q-Tip is from A Tribe Called Quest, Black Thought is from The Roots and dEnAun is from D12, where he was also known as Mr Porter and Kon Artis.
